OL,3,C19 children killed by a parent due to
OL,4,Caccess 'failings'
OL,6,FIt said the family courts were still
OL,7,F"failing to protect children" despite
OL,8,Fprevious warnings.
OL,10,FWomen's Aid chief executive Farah
OL,11,FNazeer said: "Every single one of the
OL,12,Fdeaths in this new report, as well as
OL,13,Fthose in our previous ones, were
OL,14,Fpreventable but a lack of action to
OL,15,Freform an institution that is not fit
OL,16,Ffor purpose ultimately let these
OL,17,Fchildren, and their families, down.
OL,18,FEvery case is one too many.
