OL,4,Caccess 'failings'
OL,6,FShe said: "The fact that 10 years on,
OL,7,Fmore children have been killed, and
OL,8,Fthe presumption of contact has not
OL,9,Fbeen removed legislatively or
OL,10,Fculturally is shameful and proof that
OL,11,Fsuccessive governments have failed to
OL,12,Fprotect children at risk of harm from
OL,13,Ftheir parents."
OL,15,FMs Throssell added: "These deaths were
OL,16,Fheartbreakingly preventable, and
OL,17,Faction needs to be taken to stop
OL,18,Fanymore avoidable deaths."
